<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1674,2023]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1674,1699]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Winston &amp; Woollacott" authorityYear="2009" box="[605,844,1675,1698]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="turrita">
<emphasis box="[605,844,1675,1698]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Trematooecia turrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Winston, J. E." box="[865,1034,1674,1699]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref32658" refString="Winston, J. E. (1984) Shallow-water Bryozoans of Carrie Bow Cay, Belize. American Museum Novitates, 2799, 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1984">Winston 1984</bibRefCitation>
; Winston &amp; Wollacott 2009), the morphology of the ooecium is strikingly different between 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Winston &amp; Woollacott" authorityYear="2009" box="[807,912,1711,1735]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="turrita">
<emphasis box="[807,912,1711,1735]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. turrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[965,1111,1711,1735]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="winstonae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[965,1111,1711,1735]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. winstonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1117,1177,1711,1734]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Winston &amp; Woollacott" authorityYear="2009" box="[1287,1392,1711,1735]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="turrita">
<emphasis box="[1287,1392,1711,1735]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. turrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a prominent ovicell and ectooecium with a longitudinal band of 25–38 pseudopores, 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[1132,1281,1747,1770]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="winstonae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[1132,1281,1747,1770]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. winstonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1290,1353,1747,1770]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
has an immersed ovicell and ectooecium with a longitudinal band of 3–9 large pseudopores. The species also differ in the shape of the interzooidal avicularia—linguiform in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Winston &amp; Woollacott" authorityYear="2009" box="[728,833,1819,1842]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Trematooecia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="turrita">
<emphasis box="[728,833,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. turrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, spatulate in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[983,1129,1819,1842]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="winstonae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[983,1129,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. winstonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1136,1196,1819,1842]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1674,2023]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[199,435,1854,1879]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="winstonae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[199,435,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Cigclisula winstonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[441,501,1855,1878]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Winston &amp; Hakansson" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[555,738,1854,1879]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[555,738,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the only species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Canu &amp; Bassler" authorityYear="1927" box="[1001,1116,1854,1879]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1001,1116,1854,1879]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Cigclisula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with fully immersed ooecia. Both species are distinguished by zooid size and colony size (smaller and unilamellar in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Winston &amp; Hakansson" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[1153,1337,1890,1915]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[1153,1337,1890,1915]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), frontal shield (irregularly punctured in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[522,672,1927,1951]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="winstonae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[522,672,1927,1951]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. winstonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[683,748,1927,1950]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, marginally punctured in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Winston &amp; Hakansson" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[1051,1239,1926,1951]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[1051,1239,1926,1951]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and frontal and interzooidal avicularia (present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira, 2014" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" box="[535,681,1963,1986]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="winstonae" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[535,681,1963,1986]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. winstonae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[688,750,1963,1986]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Almeida &amp; Souza &amp; Menegola &amp; Sanner &amp; Vieira" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Winston &amp; Hakansson" baseAuthorityYear="1986" box="[869,1053,1962,1987]" class="Gymnolaemata" family="Colatooeciidae" genus="Cigclisula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cheilostomatida" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Bryozoa" rank="species" species="psammophila">
<emphasis box="[869,1053,1962,1987]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">C. psammophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[245,775,1998,2023]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1436,1674,2023]" box="[245,775,1998,2023]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[245,398,1998,2023]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Distribution.</emphasis>
Caribbean: 
<collectingCountry box="[535,606,1998,2023]" name="Belize" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Belize</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[661,771,1998,2023]" name="Barbados" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Barbados</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
